object
Class Node

java.lang.Object
  object.Node

public class Node
extends java.lang.Object

Node objects consist of a label as well as co-ordinates and are used as part of connection objects to both get input and output of graphs and/or trees. Whenever a node is created it should be added to the array list of nodes.

Author:
Curtis Stokes
